claim.claim-text:
1. An aqueous formulation comprising: 
(a) a polyphenolic compound; 
(b) an amino acid; 
(c) active soluble fiber; and 
(d) an aqueous diluent.

35. A formulation that slows the absorption of sugars from mammalian intestine, said formulation comprising the elements: 
(a) a polyphenolic compound; 
(b) an amino acid; 
(c) active soluble fiber; and 
(d) an aqueous diluent, 
wherein each element is present in an amount sufficient to provide said formulation that slows said absorption of sugars.
